</table>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"2e1bffcfe942"><strong>Note:</strong> All date and time value=
s are provided in UTC using ISO 8601 format (e.g., <code>2026-04-28T14:00:0=
0Z</code>). If your property operates in a different time zone, you may nee=
d to convert these values in subsequent workflow steps.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"264d1b5c-74e4-4e4e-aad5-63f790e28fe5">
<h2 local-id=3D"c685a4a3aa8b" id=3D"ReservationCreated-HowItWorks">How It W=
orks</h2>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"733caaec-dac9-4e3f-bda4-041d429f20c8">
<li local-id=3D"0373eabb-da3f-48e1-b4ed-8de0703c63c7">
<p local-id=3D"d72ccdfd4f05">When the workflow is activated, the <strong>Re=
servation Created</strong> trigger registers itself to listen for new reser=
vation events in your property.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"75f1d13a-ed54-486b-b946-e2d2afbee4e7">
<p local-id=3D"5a7bd3afbf43">Whenever a new reservation is created in Mews =
=E2=80=94 whether through the Mews Commander, a booking engine, a channel m=
anager, or any other source =E2=80=94 the system sends an event notificatio=
n to the trigger.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abc7c804-2585-49eb-81e8-5e3bd49bc287">
<p local-id=3D"4d9f73873083">The trigger receives and validates the event t=
o ensure it is authentic and has not already been processed (duplicate even=
ts are automatically suppressed).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b9147c86-2a01-4bd4-9b1d-940f9c31d4ed">
<p local-id=3D"40b59c0b7df1">The reservation and guest details are extracte=
d and sent to the <strong>out</strong> output port, making them available t=
o the next steps in your workflow.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6110bb1d-ccad-4ed0-90ba-b17d5a05225f">
<p local-id=3D"806c2731837e">When the workflow is deactivated, the trigger =
automatically stops listening for events.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"6cc4c523b2d8"><strong>Note:</strong> The trigger includes bu=
ilt-in duplicate event suppression. If the same reservation creation event =
is received more than once (e.g., due to a retry), it will only be processe=
d once, preventing duplicate workflow executions.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"4927e6ff-7aa6-4fad-9c65-db1229bb12fb">
<h2 local-id=3D"5b144e02864c" id=3D"ReservationCreated-ExampleUseCases">Exa=
mple Use Cases</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"465c8851-4b7f-4f85-882c-ca4c2de59ddd">
<li local-id=3D"fd782f5c-1278-4fe3-923b-42eb0a19e925">
<p local-id=3D"0d024737e3d1"><strong>Welcome email</strong> =E2=80=94 When =
a new reservation is created, use the guest's email and name to send a pers=
onalized welcome or confirmation message.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"862c71ef-c0ac-4670-9920-a117e2bd7004">
<p local-id=3D"5b0364b32232"><strong>Pre-arrival task creation</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Automatically create a task (e.g., "Prepare VIP amenities") linked t=
o the reservation when a new booking comes in.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"530d02cb-072f-4c7b-8106-fd13c0ef54fe">
<p local-id=3D"ec42b1aa4488"><strong>Channel tracking</strong> =E2=80=94 Us=
e the <strong>Origin</strong> and <strong>Origin Details</strong> fields to=
 log or route reservations differently based on the booking source (e.g., d=
irect bookings vs. OTA bookings).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"fe528c49-cab5-45fa-8946-386590357ff7">
<p local-id=3D"61b3f406644c"><strong>Loyalty program handling</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Check the <strong>Guest Loyalty Code</strong> to determine if the gu=
est is a loyalty member and trigger special workflows, such as assigning ro=
om upgrades or sending exclusive offers.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b98fa3ef-72f0-404b-95e7-ac651f6fcc02">
<p local-id=3D"3dd06918af5f"><strong>CRM synchronization</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Push new reservation and guest data to an external CRM system using the gu=
est details and <strong>Guest External Identifier</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"b003e39f-9015-483d-b8f4-26ee8bdfa244">
<h2 local-id=3D"8f419862d5d1" id=3D"ReservationCreated-ImportantNotes">Impo=
rtant Notes</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"61fc74bf-299c-472c-853d-2cf=
eb24c27f8" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"dda74eff-24db-40cd-9616-75c153eefb39">
<th data-local-id=3D"b73621d1-4531-4133-b7d9-efa709497a68" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a2582652eb1b">Topic</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"39002321-4e15-4d81-b206-10433a92b9e0" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e27d905da9b3">Details</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c1fab979-3add-4afd-b38a-f587e6936f28">
<td data-local-id=3D"623e72c1-febd-48eb-a31f-c0240ca4b6ab" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c2a8dd5fc23a"><strong>One event per reservation</strong></p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a8160e1e-e49a-42e0-b8c3-b891dae64192" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7121c1452634">This trigger fires once when a reservation is =
first created. Subsequent changes to the reservation (e.g., date changes, c=
ancellations) will not fire this trigger. Use dedicated triggers for those =
events if needed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"800d3d41-934b-4a0d-a5ee-ef0b160b9806">
<td data-local-id=3D"446764cc-42e5-41fa-90e9-0b20c70cfa2c" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ba9f713f3b36"><strong>Guest fields may be empty</strong></p>=
</td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d018a19b-123f-4e76-ad27-761b428b190a" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2e7ba7756cb3">Some guest fields (email, telephone, nationali=
ty, etc.) depend on the information available at the time the reservation i=
s created. If a field has not been filled in yet, it will be empty. Conside=
r adding conditional logic in your workflow to handle missing values.</p></=
td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"47a46ac2-9fbf-4d86-ba88-5a7b2633502f">
<td data-local-id=3D"008b6a09-652e-4bb2-8fd7-2c5af47f0443" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e99aca988948"><strong>All times are in UTC</strong></p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d518386a-b4ff-4191-8fc5-737e3f24b064" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c7b510e33770">All date and time fields use UTC. If your work=
flow needs local time, add a conversion step after the trigger.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
